title: 'Athletic' Morton Ranch could present Katy issue
text: 'Athletic' Morton Ranch could present Katy issue Jimmy Galvan Sports Editor Katy Times | 0 comments When you are the second ranked state team, you normally go into every contest as the favorite. This week, Katy will take on Morton Ranch Saturday at Rhodes Stadium and the Tigers will enter this contest as the heavy favorite over the Mavericks, which just claimed its first district of the year last week with a 21-20 win over Mayde Creek. “We just have to concentrate and play our game and that is just where we are at in district,” said Katy Head Football Coach Gary Joseph. “We have to be able to execute and we have to be able to run our offense.
